==English==
===Etymology===
From the French ''[[sauter]]'' meaning ''to jump'', because the cook shakes the pan to make the food jump up so it doesn't stick.

{{rfp}}
===Pronunciation===
*saw-tay'

===Verb===
'''sauté'''
#To cook quickly in an open pan with little fat.

